name: EB-002-Lennon
description:
John Winston Ono Lennon MBE (Liverpool, October 9, 1940 – New York, December 8, 1980) was a British singer, songwriter and peace activist who founded the Beatles, the most successful band commercial in the history of popular music. His songwriting partnership with bandmate Paul McCartney was one of the most celebrated in music history. Along with George Harrison and Ringo Starr, the group achieved worldwide fame during the 1960s. In 1969, Lennon started the Plastic Ono Band with his second wife, Yoko Ono, and continued to pursue a solo career after the Beatles split in April 1970.
